records.addlTxt:
11:46 AM Defendant David S Brinn in court, in custody, with attorney Anna M Kees.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case called for plea and sentencing.
State places offer on the record.
Court conducts plea colloquy.

COURT ORDERS THE FOLLOWING:
Total Prison:  12 YEARS
Initial Confinement:  6 YEARS
Extended Supervision:  6 YEARS
48  Days Credit.

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety;  
No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed;
No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores);
Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel in Waukesha County within 6 months of release from custody;
Do not drive or operate a motor vehicle without a valid license, comply with all licensing restrictions;
DNA sample to be provided;

D/L REVOCATION: 36 months.
IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

FINE: $1,569 
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $250
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $50 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to Village of Menomonee Falls Police Department or to be converted to a civil judgment for non payment of fee.

*Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
